parameters: \unknown\msgevent[1]\lspi[120]Thank you so much for taking care of those bad guys,\. Lyon!
\unknown\msgevent[1]\lspi[120]Here are some items that might help you out!
\unknown\msgevent[1]\lspi[120]Go stop the bandits!\. You're the town's hope!
\unknown\msgevent[17]\lspi[120]Those people are way too co-ordinated to be ordinary bandits.
\unknown\lspi[120]\msgevent[17]I'm not sure I can stand up to them alone.\..\..
\unknown\msgevent[17]\lspi[120]This nauseating feeling.\..\..\. Wait, I've felt this before.
\unknown\lspi[120]\msgevent[17]It's the same as that day ten years ago!
\unknown\lspi[120]\msgevent[17]No.\..\..\. Why does it have to be now!? Mom,\. dad,\. please.\..\..
\n<Greedy Bandit>\msgevent[18]You got a pretty face,\. the kind that can easily sell for thousands.
\n<Greedy Bandit>\msgevent[18]Now hold still, you'll depreciate if you get hurt.
\unknown\lspi[120]\msgevent[17](Oh no,\. I can't shake that feeling earlier.\.\. There's no way I can deal with him right now.)
\Lyon\unknown\msgevent[19]A slave trading bandit huh?\.\. Is looting not enough for you people?
\n<Greedy Bandit>\msgevent[18]What can I say?\.\. Times are tough and the money's good.
\n<Greedy Bandit>\msgevent[18]There's no demand for meddling brats,\. so I'll leave you to my friends.
\n<Preaching Bandit>\msgevent[21]Hey kid,\. the world ain't all sunshine and rainbows OK?
\n<Preaching Bandit>\msgevent[21]Take your morals and ideals with you,\. TO THE GRAVE!
\n<Preaching Bandit>\msgevent[21]Y-\.you bring him back RIGHT NOW!
\lyon\unknown\msgevent[19]Let's hope you wise up and surrender.
Would it be a good idea to loot his possessions?
You managed to find 25 Coins on his person!
He's no longer conscious nor useful.
